</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="24" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1039,1426]" pageId="2" pageNumber="24">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,266,1039,1065]" pageId="2" pageNumber="24">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. Members of the species-group are similar to those of the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Benedek &amp; Volynkin &amp; Babics &amp; Saldaitis" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Owada" baseAuthorityYear="1981" box="[933,1107,1039,1065]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Polymixis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="khumbuensis">
<emphasis box="[933,1107,1039,1065]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="24">P. khumbuensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species-group but are distinguished by the medial area which is of the same colour as the subbasal and the postmedial areas (in the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Benedek &amp; Volynkin &amp; Babics &amp; Saldaitis" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Owada" baseAuthorityYear="1981" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Polymixis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="khumbuensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="24">P. khumbuensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species-group, the medial area is darker than other areas of the forewing), the nearly straight antemedial line (it is sinuous in the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Benedek &amp; Volynkin &amp; Babics &amp; Saldaitis" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Owada" baseAuthorityYear="1981" box="[314,487,1147,1173]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Polymixis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="khumbuensis">
<emphasis box="[314,487,1147,1173]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="24">P. khumbuensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species-group), and the smooth outer margin of the postmedial line which is dentate in the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Benedek &amp; Volynkin &amp; Babics &amp; Saldaitis" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Owada" baseAuthorityYear="1981" box="[221,393,1183,1209]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Polymixis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="khumbuensis">
<emphasis box="[221,393,1183,1209]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="24">P. khumbuensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species-group. Additionally, the outer forewing margin of the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Benedek &amp; Volynkin &amp; Babics &amp; Saldaitis" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Moore" baseAuthorityYear="1881" box="[1089,1248,1183,1209]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Polymixis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="albosignata">
<emphasis box="[1089,1248,1183,1209]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="24">P. albosignata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species-group is less wavy than in the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Benedek &amp; Volynkin &amp; Babics &amp; Saldaitis" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Owada" baseAuthorityYear="1981" box="[389,560,1219,1245]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Polymixis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="khumbuensis">
<emphasis box="[389,560,1219,1245]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="24">P. khumbuensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species-group. The male genitalia of the species-group differ from those of the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Benedek &amp; Volynkin &amp; Babics &amp; Saldaitis" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Moore" baseAuthorityYear="1867" box="[151,272,1255,1281]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Mamestra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="albirena">
<emphasis box="[151,272,1255,1281]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="24">P. albirena</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Benedek &amp; Volynkin &amp; Babics &amp; Saldaitis" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Owada" baseAuthorityYear="1981" box="[325,496,1255,1281]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Polymixis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="khumbuensis">
<emphasis box="[325,496,1255,1281]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="24">P. khumbuensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species-groups by the markedly smaller clavi, the more prominent dorsal costal protrusion, the stronger setae on the cucullus forming a corona (absent in the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Benedek &amp; Volynkin &amp; Babics &amp; Saldaitis" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Moore" baseAuthorityYear="1867" box="[988,1110,1291,1317]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Mamestra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="albirena">
<emphasis box="[988,1110,1291,1317]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="24">P. albirena</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Benedek &amp; Volynkin &amp; Babics &amp; Saldaitis" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Owada" baseAuthorityYear="1981" box="[1166,1339,1291,1317]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Polymixis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="khumbuensis">
<emphasis box="[1166,1339,1291,1317]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="24">P. khumbuensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
speciesgroups), the stronger asymmetry of digiti, the somewhat more elongate sacculi, and the aedeagus having more elongate carina and vesica. The female genitalia are characterized by the elongate ventral medial process of the antrum (the similar process is present only in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Benedek &amp; Volynkin &amp; Babics &amp; Saldaitis" authorityYear="2021" box="[577,725,1399,1425]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Polymixis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pateikkaya">
<emphasis box="[577,725,1399,1425]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="24">P. pateikkaya</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but in the latter species it is conspicuously less elongate).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
